title: Horrendous Vs. Hilarious
body:
I’m so happy to be writing a cute Stony prompt like this!!! I love it! Thanks anon!!!! I hope you enjoy it!

He really didn’t know how he’d gotten himself into this horrendous situation. That’s all it was. Horrendous. Although, Tony didn’t seem to share his opinion. He thought it was hilarious. At least, that’s the impression Steve got, seeing the love of his life on the floor clutching his stomach, laughing like he was programmed to do it. 

The situation that he had gotten himself into was a rather…precarious one. Also horrendous, had he mentioned that? He was stuck…in the iron man suit. Tony had mentioned something about wanting to test some adjustments he had made to the suit, and of course Steve, being the good boyfriend he was, volunteered to help. Tony was eager to have him in the shop, in hindsight, maybe a little too eager. He had come into the lab, and Tony was immediately rushing him into the suit. At first, Steve didn’t expect anything negative to come from it. Tony got this way sometimes, especially when he had a breakthrough. So, he got in the suit. It fit well, it was comfortable. Tony started asking him questions about the suit, how it looked, temperature, how it felt…overall. That’s when Steve started to get suspicious. As he started to make his way out of the suit, he realized his arms were stuck, and so were his legs. 

“Tony. I think we have a problem.”

“Yeah? What’s up?” 

“…I’m stuck.” Cue laughter. 

“….You’re stuhuck?? This is great.” 

“No. No, it’s really not. Get me out of this.” 

“Steve. I didn’t tell it to do that. I don’t know what’s going on. Let me go take a look.” Tony ran over to his computers and started to look through some programs, meanwhile Steve’s situation only continued to get worse. 

The suit started to vibrate. Kinda like a phone, but a hell of a lot more intense, which meant absolute hell for Steve. 

“TONY!!!! PROBLEM!!” Tony looked back at Steve, only to see his face red and his lips pressed together. 

“What’s going on? Is it hurting you?!” Steve’s head shook back and forth rapidly. 

“Then what’s the problem?” 

“I-ihit’s vibrahahating!” 

“…Are you saying it’s tickling you?” Tony put his hand over his mouth, trying to stifle his laughter. 

“NOT FUNNY!! HEHEHELP!!!” Tony laughed out loud at this, and then a devious idea popped into his head, he knew how ticklish his boyfriend was, and he definitely knew how to make it worse for him. 

“Awww, poor super soldier, can’t take a little tickling?” As Tony teased him, Steve felt as if the sensations against his whole body intensified. He screamed out through his laughter, begging Tony to make it stop. 

“Aww, but you’re so cute! Squirming and laughing like that.” Again, the sensations seemed to worsen at Tony’s teasing words. He started to gather up his strength, and started to pull against the restraints on his arms and legs. 

Tony walked up to his lover and started to drum his fingers on his sides, and occassionally would run them up into his armpits. 

Eventually he stopped and started to make his way over to his computer, all the while listening to Steve cracking up at the sensations lighting up his body. 

Tony pulled up the program to shut down his suit, but before he could shut it down, he heard the sound of metal ripping and circuits breaking. He looked over and saw his suit partially shredded, and Steve with his hands on his knees, and sweat dripping off his head. 

“Oh my god. Are you okay?” Tony ran over to him and started to rub his back, trying to help him get some air back into his lungs. 

“God I’m sorry, I didn’t realize it was that bad.” He was so busy apologizing that he didn’t notice Steve’s fast recovery, until he felt hands on his arms and pushing him towards a wall. 

“Am I okay? Am I okay? I was just TORTURED by one of your suits! No, I’m not okay, but I will be. After I get something.” Tony’s eyes widened, and he didn’t hesitate to ask, 

“What do you need?” 

“REVENGE!” The rest of their afternoon was filled with laughter and love, all stemming from a horrendous and hilarious situation for both of them.

summary: 97 and 72 Thorbruce for the 100 word writing prompt thing?
question: 97 and 72 Thorbruce for the 100 word writing prompt thing?
answer:
Thank you! 

Bruce came into Thor and his living room and faceplanted on the couch. Thor was sitting in the chair next to it.

‘You’re still in your raincoat,’ Thor commented.

‘I’m aware,’ mumbled Bruce.

‘Rough day?’

Bruce groaned, ‘Yeah. And my zipper’s stuck.’

‘Your zipper’s… okay, get up, I’ll help,’ said Thor with a small smile. Bruce pulled himself up to his feet, and walking over to where Thor was sitting.

Thor reached over, trying to zip down the zipper of the raincoat, but it was very, very stuck.

‘Today really sucks and now I’m trapped in my own coat,’ muttered Bruce.

Thor smiled empathetically, standing up and giving Bruce a kiss. ‘Don’t worry, we’ll get you out.’

Bruce sighed, before Thor gave the zipper a giant tug in a last, futile attempt. The zipper definitely budged, but also ripped it right off.

‘…At least you’re not trapped,’ said Thor sheepishly.

‘I suppose you’re right,’ Bruce replied with a slight smile.

Bruce came into Thor and his living room and faceplanted on the couch. Thor was sitting in the chair next to it.

‘You’re still in your raincoat,’ Thor commented.

[[MORE]]

‘I’m aware,’ mumbled Bruce.

‘Rough day?’

Bruce groaned, ‘Yeah. And my zipper’s stuck.’

‘Your zipper’s… okay, get up, I’ll help,’ said Thor with a small smile. Bruce pulled himself up to his feet, and walking over to where Thor was sitting.

Thor reached over, trying to zip down the zipper of the raincoat, but it was very, very stuck.

‘Today really sucks and now I’m trapped in my own coat,’ muttered Bruce.

Thor smiled empathetically, standing up and giving Bruce a kiss. ‘Don’t worry, we’ll get you out.’

Bruce sighed, before Thor gave the zipper a giant tug in a last, futile attempt. The zipper definitely budged, but also ripped it right off.

‘…At least you’re not trapped,’ said Thor sheepishly.

‘I suppose you’re right,’ Bruce replied with a slight smile.

summary: Where would you suggest to start with Cap's comics for someone who never read ANYTHING?
question: Where would you suggest to start with Cap's comics for someone who never read ANYTHING?
answer:
Hi @giuliawithag - I love these types of questions! Yay! Hands down Mark Waid’s “Man Out of Time” is the best place to start. The reason I always suggest this little series as an entry point is because it’s a modern retelling of the Avengers finding Steve on the ice, so it covers his entry and adjustment into the 21st century (something the MCU largely left out). It’s written by Mark Waid, who has one of the best Steve Rogers voices in all of Marvel. And it’s relatively short (5 issues) so it’s not too intimidating. It’s really a brilliant little series.

Don’t tell anyone I told you this, but you can find it for free here (I have no idea if this series, which was released in 2011, can be found on Marvel Unlimited so that’s why I’m linking you). Just have a really good pop-up blocker on because this site is the best there is for finding any comic you want to find - it’s the largest library I know of anyway - but it’s pop-up ads are atrocious and many of them nsfw. 

Once you’re done with this little series let me know and I’ll walk you through Cap writers Englehart, Stern, Gruenwald, (the rest of) Waid, Brubaker and the new one being written by Coates, if you would like. 

Welcome to the world of comics, my friend!
